description:
Have you ever wondered how to read the Bible effectively in order to get closer to God? In this message, we look at simple ways to study the Word so that it becomes alive. What about Biblical meditation? Joshua 1:8 says, “This book of the law shall not depart out of thy mouth; but thou shalt meditate therein day and night....” Learn about the four steps the Hebrews took when reading Scripture: 1. Memorize Scripture. 2. Imagine yourself in the story. 3. Study the words deeply and consider their application to you. 4. Share and discuss what you learn.
